5wy.title: Project outline: Intro to the Universal Property
5wy.clickbait: Outline detailing all the work required for a proposed Arbital Project
5wy.text:
This page is for brainstorming about the outline for the [5wh]. We want to make as complete a list as we can ahead of time of the pages that will be required for the project. This project should be finishable in a week's time, so its scope should be pretty narrow. We'll only target [1r7] level for the first iteration.

# Possible arc #1

1. The idea of [ not caring about things except up to isomorphism].
- [4f4]
2. The idea that [ we can describe objects based entirely on how they interact with other objects].
3. Introduce the [ category of finite sets], describing the empty set, disjoint union and product
- [3jz]
- [finite_set]
- [empty_set]
- [5s8]
- [set_disjoint_union]
- [set_product]
4. Show how [ the empty set can be described entirely by its universal property].
- [universal_property]
5. Show how [ the union and product can be described entirely by their universal properties], up to isomorphism.
6. Introduce a specific [3rb poset] category: [ $\mathbb{N}$ with an arrow between $a$ and $b$ iff $a$ divides $b$]. (Not sure about this one - maybe it already requires knowing what a category is?)
7. Describe [ the least upper bound and greatest lower bounds] in a poset; in particular, in $\mathbb{N}$ under the divisibility relation, we obtain the GCD and the LCM.
- A page (or two) about [-least_upper_bound] and [-greatest_lower_bound]
8. Describe [ the universal properties of the LUB and GLB]; compare them with the union and coproduct.
9. Wrap up by [ explaining that this kind of property crops up all over the place].

# Possible arc #2

1. *Feel free to add your own outline arc ideas*

5zq.clickbait: Collecting all project proposals under this page.

5zr.title: Universal property of the empty set
5zr.clickbait: The empty set can be characterised by how it interacts with other sets, rather than by any explicit property of the empty set itself.

5zs.title: Set product
5zs.clickbait: A fundamental way of combining sets is to take their product, making a set that contains all tuples of elements from the originals.

5zt.title: Object identity via interactions
5zt.clickbait: If we think of objects as opaque "black boxes", how can we tell whether two objects are different? By looking at how they interact with other objects!

5zv.title: Universal property of the product
5zv.clickbait: The product can be defined in a very general way, applicable to the natural numbers, to sets, to algebraic structures, and so on.

5zy.title: Finite set
5zy.clickbait: A finite set is one which is not infinite. Some of these are the least complicated sets.

63m.title: Universal property of the disjoint union
63m.clickbait: Just as the empty set may be described by a universal property, so too may the disjoint union of sets.

65z.title: Greatest lower bound in a poset
65z.clickbait: The greatest lower bound is an abstraction of the idea of the greatest common divisor to a general poset.

76k.title: Universal property of joins and meets in a poset
76k.clickbait: Partially ordered sets are a good setting to illustrate some of the concepts of category theory; joins and meets are instances of category-theoretic ideas.
